# =============================================================================
# .claude version control — ALLOWLIST (deny-by-default)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Everything is ignored unless explicitly un-ignored below. This guarantees
# that secrets and runtime data Claude Code writes here can never be committed
# by accident. To start tracking something new, add a `!` line for it.
# =============================================================================

# Ignore every top-level entry by default.
/*

# --- Tracked: your customizations -------------------------------------------
!/.gitignore
!/.gitattributes
!/agents/
!/skills/
!/commands/
!/scripts/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Intentionally NOT tracked (kept here as documentation of what we exclude):
#   .credentials.json        OAuth tokens / secrets  -> NEVER commit
#   settings.json            global config           -> excluded by choice
#   settings.local.json      machine-local config    -> NEVER commit
#   projects/                session data (277M+)    -> huge churn
#   history.jsonl            prompt history
#   file-history/            file snapshots (12M+)
#   transcripts/             session transcripts
#   plugins/                 reinstallable plugins
#   shell-snapshots/ cache/ logs/ debug/ daemon/ backups/ ... runtime noise
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
